# Test Ticket API Endpoints

### 1. Create a new ticket (POST /api/tickets)
POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/tickets
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Test ticket",
  "description": "This is a test ticket",
  "category": "Bug",
  "priority": "high"
}

###

### 2. Get ticket list (GET /api/tickets)
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/tickets?page=1&size=10
Accept: application/json

###

### 3. Get single ticket by ID (GET /api/tickets/{id})
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/tickets/1
Accept: application/json

###

### 4. Get non-existent ticket (should return 404)
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/tickets/999999
Accept: application/json

###

### 5. Update ticket (PUT /api/tickets/{id})
PUT http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/tickets/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Updated ticket title",
  "description": "Updated description",
  "status": "in_progress",
  "priority": "urgent"
}

###

### 6. Update non-existent ticket (should return 404)
PUT http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/tickets/999999
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "This should fail"
}

###

### 7. Delete ticket (DELETE /api/tickets/{id})
DELETE http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/tickets/1
Accept: application/json

###

### 8. Delete non-existent ticket (should return 404)
DELETE http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/tickets/999999
Accept: application/json

###
